    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It definitely needs to. \n\nAn explanation in four parts:\n- there are folks that want grpc insecurely but don't want to link in OpenSSL - this probably isn't a use case for many of our wrapped languages, which have huge environments anyway - but will be useful for folks wanting to run in very constrained environments\n- the fake_ credentials should probably be dropped from public API's, as they're really just for testing (@jboeuf - if you don't disagree I'll file bugs)\n- knowing we need none of the security infrastructure allows optimizations and simplifications that aren't possible otherwise - and we have some users that need this too\n- there are situations where the raw wire protocol provides perfectly adequate security (e.g. via a unix domain socket), and having such a mechanism seems important\n"
  },
