    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I agree with Craig.\n\nFake transport security adds a dummy handshake and some framing to (think additional mallocs / copies). It was really useful to put it in the public API at some point because we could test the \"secure path\" without having to go through SSL (which helped us debug some node issues for example). However it looks like things have now settled down and I'm OK removing it from the public API.\n"
